🛡️ Automated Digital Forensics and Investigation using Autopsy

📌 Project Overview

This project demonstrates digital forensic analysis using Autopsy, an open source tool used for investigating and analyzing digital evidence. The objective is to examine disk images and file systems to recover, analyze, and interpret data for forensic purposes.

Autopsy is widely used in cybersecurity, law enforcement, and incident response to uncover hidden or deleted information.

🎯 Objectives

Perform digital forensic investigation on a system image
Recover deleted files and analyze artifacts
Understand file system structures and metadata
Identify suspicious activities and user behavior
Generate forensic reports for analysis

🧠 Concept

Digital forensics involves collecting and analyzing digital evidence to investigate security incidents or cyber crimes.

Autopsy works by
Analyzing disk images and file systems
Extracting artifacts such as files, logs, and browser data
Recovering deleted or hidden data
Providing a structured view of evidence

