🚀 Implementation Steps

🔹 1. Installation and Setup

Installed Autopsy using package manager or official installer

Command for Kali
sudo apt update
sudo apt install autopsy -y

Launched using
autopsy

🔹 2. Case Creation

Created a new forensic case
Defined case name, directory, and investigator details

🔹 3. Add Data Source

Loaded disk image or local drive
Supported formats include raw images and logical drives

🔹 4. Ingest Modules Selection

Enabled modules such as
File type identification
Keyword search
Recent activity
Hash lookup

🔹 5. Data Processing

Autopsy analyzed the data source and extracted artifacts

🔹 6. Evidence Analysis

Explored files, directories, and metadata
Identified suspicious or deleted files

🔹 7. Reporting

Generated structured forensic reports

